title: Bulldogs Shut Out Wildcats at Home
text:
Bulldogs Shut Out Wildcats at Home 
By Norman Seawright III October 9, 2015 Updated Oct 9, 2015 at 10:45 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) -- The University of Minnesota-Duluth (UMD) women's soccer team scored a Northern Sun Intercollegiate Conference (NSIC) win to kick off homecoming weekend. 
The lone goal of the game came from Natalie St. Martin, while Jordan Melby's six saves gave the Bulldogs a shutout over the visiting Wayne State Wildcats.
